  "prompt": "How do I get my songs converted to karaoke or instrumental?",
  "response": "Converting songs to karaoke or instrumental versions can be done using various tools and methods. Here are some options:\n\n### Online Tools and Software:\n1. **LALAL.AI:** This online service uses AI to separate vocals from accompaniment. You can upload your song, and it will provide you with the instrumental/karaoke version.\n   \n2. **Vocalremover.org:** Another free online tool that allows you to upload your music track and removes the vocals, leaving you with an instrumental.\n\n3. **Spleeter by Deezer:** A powerful open-source tool that can separate vocals and instruments from a track. You can use it by installing it on your computer and running it from the command line.\n\n4. **Audacity:** A free, open-source audio editing software. Though more manual than AI-driven tools, it can separate vocals using various techniques like phase cancellation.\n\n### Steps using Audacity:\n1. **Import the Song:** Open Audacity and import the song you want to convert.\n2. **Split the Track:** Separate the stereo track into two mono tracks.\n3. **Invert One Track:** Select one of the tracks and use the 'Invert' effect.\n4. **Combine Tracks:** After inverting, combine the two tracks into one stereo track.\n5. **Remove Vocals:** Fine-tune the settings to minimize vocals.\n\n### Professional Services:\nIf you prefer a high-quality output and don\u2019t mind paying, you can seek the help of professional audio engineers or services like:\n1. **iZotope RX:** A professional suite of audio editing tools that includes features for isolating vocals.\n2. **Hire Freelancers:** Platforms like Fiverr or Upwork have audio engineers who can professionally create karaoke versions of your songs.\n\n### Mobile Apps:\n1. **Moises:** Available on iOS and Android, it uses AI to separate vocals and instruments.\n2. **Karaoke Anything:** This app also helps in converting songs into karaoke tracks by removing the vocals.\n\n### Summary:\nChoose the method that best matches your needs and technical comfort level. Online tools and software like LALAL.AI and Audacity offer free or low-cost solutions for personal projects, while professional services and mobile apps might be better for higher-quality outputs.",
